<br>
Let us not forget the children that are now without a mother, father, grandparents, uncles, aunts, cousins or friends.<br>
<br>
Let us not forget the potential number of lives that could have been lost in the World Trade Centers alone was somewhere near 40,000.<br>
<br>
Let us not forget we are Americans and we will stand up to a challenge.<br>
<br>
While we must not forget, we also need to push forward - ever determined to live our lives not in terror but with resolve.<br>
<br>
Resolve to remember those that ran into burning buildings trying to help, only to lose their lives.<br>
<br>
Resolve to remember those that searched 3 different sites for signs of life.<br>
<br>
Resolve to stand by those in uniform that are doing all they can to find the people responsible and bring them justice.<br>
<br>
Resolve to make this world a better place for our children.<br>
<br>
No, we will not forget but there are some that will wish to their god we would. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/uizreel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izreel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/11/02 3:22:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=391.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Remember...</span><hr size=1> watched the clip again...<br>
