<br>
If I had only known I would have saluted you while I had the chance. Personally, I am no where near New York. I am in Chicago. But here in Chicago we also have a pretty tall building (and potential target) in the Sears Tower. Everytime I drive into the city I imagine what it would be like to simply not have it there anymore. And then to imagine the devastation downtown if it were to fall. It makes me tear up. Like everyone else said, my heart goes out to you and the rest of New York City for having to endure this senseless act of murder. I remember being told about it as I came into the office. Someone said &quot;Hey did you hear a couple of planes hit the world trade center?&quot; And Im like &quot;Ok...and? Whats the punchline?&quot; Then I went to the kitchen and saw the live feed of both towers on fire. And I went into a state of shock. I remember saying out loud something really really stupid. I said &quot;Well...I bet this will be bigger than Oklahoma.&quot; I still feel bad for being so insensitive. We were eventually evacuated from downtown and I went home. All I wanted to do was keep the TV on and play EQ all day. For once EQ wasnt able to hide my pain and shock, like it usually does in regular situations. All I know now is I will never be able to, nor want to, ever forget any detail. Certain people need to be brought to justice and I want it to be sooner than later. That is all.<br>
<br>
Sdace Windrunner<br>
